{{Politics of Pakistan}} The '''Council Muslim League''' was a faction of the [[Pakistan Muslim League]] that divided from the [[Convention Muslim League]] that was supportive of the military regime of the [[President of Pakistan]] Gen. [[Ayub Khan (Field Marshal)|Ayub Khan]].<ref name="Burki">{{cite book|title=Historical Dictionary of Pakistan|first=Shahid Javed|last=Burki|authorlink=Shahid Javed Burki|page=148|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=9781442241480|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rk-sBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA148}}</ref> Sardar Muhammad Zafarullah, [[Mian Mumtaz Daultana]], Sardar Shauket Hyat-Khan, Chaudhry Muhammad Husain Chattha, [[Khawaja Muhammad Safdar]] and [[Chaudhry Zahoor Elahi]] were prominent leaders of the Council Muslim League.
